6.Symmetric difference.

-two sets which has common elements in it gets eliminated here

s1 = {1, 2, 3, 4}
s2 = {3, 4, 5, 6}
Only in s1:    {1, 2}
Common:        {3, 4}
Only in s2:    {5, 6}
Symmetric Difference
= {1, 2, 5, 6}



# 1st approach
s1 = {1, 2, 3, 4}
s2 = {3, 4, 5, 6}
result = set()
for i in s1:
    if i not in s2:
        result.add(i)

for i in s2:
    if i not in s1:
        result.add(i)
print(result)

o/p-->{1, 2, 5, 6}
TC = O(n + m)
SC = O(n + m)



#2nd approach
print(s1 ^ s2)
TC = O(n + m)
SC = O(n + m)



print(s1.symmetric_difference(s2))
TC = O(n + m)
SC = O(n + m)
